OL,3,CThe mum helping to save hundreds of
OL,4,Clives in son's memory
OL,6,FPrevious medical tests failed to spot
OL,7,Fthat he had arrhythmogenic right
OL,8,Fventricular cardiomyopathy, a rare
OL,9,Fcondition that causes the heart muscle
OL,10,Fto be replaced by fatty tissue.
OL,12,F"I just heard the most horrendous
OL,13,Fscream," Deborah explains. "I knew
OL,14,Finstantly that something was wrong. I
OL,15,Fgrabbed the phone and called 999. The
OL,16,Fparamedics arrived but we had already
OL,17,Flost Aaron."
