OL,3,CThe mum helping to save hundreds of
OL,4,Clives in son's memory
OL,6,FAfter finding out that more than 600
OL,7,Fyoung people die of similar
OL,8,Fundiagnosed conditions every year,
OL,9,FDeborah set up a fund in her son's
OL,10,Fname, with the charity Cardiac Risk in
OL,11,Fthe Young, to get more young people
OL,12,Fscreenings.
OL,14,F"10 to 15 minutes will give you that
OL,15,Fpiece of mind", she said. "That's all
OL,16,Fit takes. I think all young people
OL,17,Fshould be screened but unfortunately
OL,18,Fthere's no national programme. That's
OL,19,Fthe reason why I do what I do."
